<!-- Baby Care Guide for New Moms -->
<section class="bcg-page">
  <style>
    .bcg-page {
      background: #fff;
      padding-bottom: 32px;
    }

    .bcg-hero {
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #FFF0F6 0%, #F0F8FF 100%);
      padding: 40px 20px 32px;
      text-align: center;
      border-bottom: 1px solid #FFD6EA;
    }

    .bcg-hero-icon { font-size: 52px; margin-bottom: 12px; display: block; }
    .bcg-hero-title { font-size: 26px; font-weight: 900; color: #1a1a1a; margin: 0 0 10px; line-height: 1.2; }
    .bcg-hero-subtitle { font-size: 14px; color: #666; line-height: 1.6; max-width: 340px; margin: 0 auto; }
    .bcg-hero-badge { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px; background: #FF69B4; color: white; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; padding: 5px 14px; border-radius: 20px; margin-top: 16px; letter-spacing: 0.4px; }

    .bcg-body { padding: 20px 16px; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 20px; }

    .bcg-card { background: #fff; border-radius: 16px; overflow: hidden; box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(0,0,0,0.07); border: 1px solid #f0f0f0; }
    .bcg-card-header { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 12px; padding: 16px; background: linear-gradient(135deg, #FFF5F9 0%, #FFF0F0 100%); border-bottom: 1px solid #FFE4EF; }
    .bcg-card-header.blue { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #F0F8FF 0%, #E8F4FF 100%); border-bottom-color: #C8E6FF; }
    .bcg-card-header.green { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #F0FFF4 0%, #E8FFF0 100%); border-bottom-color: #B8F0C8; }
    .bcg-card-header.yellow { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #FFFBF0 0%, #FFF8E0 100%); border-bottom-color: #FFE88A; }
    .bcg-card-icon { font-size: 28px; width: 44px; height: 44px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; background: white; border-radius: 12px; box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.08); flex-shrink: 0; }
    .bcg-card-title { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 800; color: #1a1a1a; margin: 0; }
    .bcg-card-subtitle { font-size: 11px; color: #888; margin: 2px 0 0; }
    .bcg-card-body { padding: 16px; }

    .bcg-tip { display: flex; gap: 12px; align-items: flex-start; padding: 10px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid #f5f5f5; }
    .bcg-tip:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
    .bcg-tip-num { width: 24px; height: 24px; background: #FF69B4; color: white; border-radius: 50%; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 800; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; flex-shrink: 0; margin-top: 1px; }
    .bcg-tip-num.blue { background: #5BA8FF; }
    .bcg-tip-num.green { background: #4CAF7D; }
    .bcg-tip-num.yellow { background: #F4B400; }
    .bcg-tip-text { font-size: 13px; color: #333; line-height: 1.6; flex: 1; }
    .bcg-tip-text strong { color: #1a1a1a; font-weight: 700; }

    .bcg-warning { background: #FFF3CD; border-left: 4px solid #F4B400; border-radius: 0 10px 10px 0; padding: 14px; display: flex; gap: 10px; align-items: flex-start; }
    .bcg-warning-icon { font-size: 20px; flex-shrink: 0; }
    .bcg-warning-text { font-size: 13px; color: #5a4500; line-height: 1.6; }

    .bcg-age-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 10px; }
    .bcg-age-card { background: #f9f9f9; border-radius: 10px; padding: 12px; border: 1px solid #eee; }
    .bcg-age-label { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; color: #FF69B4; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.5px; margin-bottom: 6px; }
    .bcg-age-items { font-size: 12px; color: #555; line-height: 1.8; }

    .bcg-back-btn { display: block; margin: 4px 16px 0; padding: 14px; background: linear-gradient(135deg, #FF69B4 0%, #FF1493 100%); color: white; text-align: center; text-decoration: none; border-radius: 12px; font-size: 14px; font-weight: 800; letter-spacing: 0.3px; box-shadow: 0 4px 16px rgba(255, 105, 180, 0.3); }
  </style>

  <div class="bcg-hero">
    <span class="bcg-hero-icon">👶</span>
    <h1 class="bcg-hero-title">New Mom's Complete<br>Baby Care Guide</h1>
    <p class="bcg-hero-subtitle">Expert-backed tips from pediatricians and experienced mothers to keep your little one safe and healthy.</p>
    <span class="bcg-hero-badge">✓ Reviewed by Pediatric Experts</span>
  </div>

  <div class="bcg-body">

    <div class="bcg-card">
      <div class="bcg-card-header">
        <div class="bcg-card-icon">🛡️</div>
        <div>
          <p class="bcg-card-title">Choosing Safe Baby Products</p>
          <p class="bcg-card-subtitle">What to look for on every label</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="bcg-card-body">
        <div class="bcg-tip"><div class="bcg-tip-num">1</div><p class="bcg-tip-text"><strong>Fragrance-free is best.</strong> Baby skin is 20–30% thinner than adult skin. Choose products labeled "fragrance-free," not just "unscented."</p></div>
        <div class="bcg-tip"><div class="bcg-tip-num">2</div><p class="bcg-tip-text"><strong>Check for hypoallergenic certification.</strong> Look for dermatologist-tested labels, especially for wipes, lotions, and detergents.</p></div>
        <div class="bcg-tip"><div class="bcg-tip-num">3</div><p class="bcg-tip-text"><strong>Avoid parabens & sulfates.</strong> These can disrupt hormones and irritate sensitive skin.</p></div>
        <div class="bcg-tip"><div class="bcg-tip-num">4</div><p class="bcg-tip-text"><strong>pH balanced formulas.</strong> Baby skin has a delicate pH of ~5.5. Use products formulated to maintain this balance.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bcg-card">
      <div class="bcg-card-header blue">
        <div class="bcg-card-icon">🌸</div>
        <div>
          <p class="bcg-card-title">Daily Skincare Routine</p>
          <p class="bcg-card-subtitle">Keep that precious skin healthy</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="bcg-card-body">
        <div class="bcg-tip"><div class="bcg-tip-num blue">1</div><p class="bcg-tip-text"><strong>Bath every 2–3 days.</strong> Daily baths can dry out newborn skin. Sponge baths between full baths keep baby fresh.</p></div>
        <div class="bcg-tip"><div class="bcg-tip-num blue">2</div><p class="bcg-tip-text"><strong>Moisturize within 3 minutes of bath.</strong> Pat skin dry (don't rub) and apply baby lotion immediately to lock in moisture.</p></div>
        <div class="bcg-tip"><div class="bcg-tip-num blue">3</div><p class="bcg-tip-text"><strong>Diaper cream at every change.</strong> Apply a zinc oxide barrier cream to prevent diaper rash before it starts.</p></div>
        <div class="bcg-tip"><div class="bcg-tip-num blue">4</div><p class="bcg-tip-text"><strong>Keep nails short.</strong> Baby nails grow fast. Trim with baby scissors after a bath when nails are softer.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bcg-warning">
      <span class="bcg-warning-icon">⚠️</span>
      <p class="bcg-warning-text"><strong>Never use adult products on babies.</strong> Adult shampoos and creams have pH levels that can seriously damage your baby's skin barrier. Always buy products made specifically for infants.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bcg-card">
      <div class="bcg-card-header yellow">
        <div class="bcg-card-icon">📅</div>
        <div>
          <p class="bcg-card-title">Age-by-Age Product Guide</p>
          <p class="bcg-card-subtitle">Right products at the right stage</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="bcg-card-body">
        <div class="bcg-age-grid">
          <div class="bcg-age-card"><div class="bcg-age-label">0–3 Months</div><div class="bcg-age-items">Gentle wash<br>Baby lotion<br>Nappy cream<br>Cotton wipes</div></div>
          <div class="bcg-age-card"><div class="bcg-age-label">3–6 Months</div><div class="bcg-age-items">Teething toys<br>Baby shampoo<br>Sunscreen SPF30<br>Soft hairbrush</div></div>
          <div class="bcg-age-card"><div class="bcg-age-label">6–12 Months</div><div class="bcg-age-items">Baby toothbrush<br>Training cup<br>Stage 1 foods<br>Safety gates</div></div>
          <div class="bcg-age-card"><div class="bcg-age-label">12–24 Months</div><div class="bcg-age-items">Fluoride toothpaste<br>Step stool<br>Learning toys<br>Potty trainer</div></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bcg-card">
      <div class="bcg-card-header green">
        <div class="bcg-card-icon">✅</div>
        <div>
          <p class="bcg-card-title">5 Mistakes to Avoid</p>
          <p class="bcg-card-subtitle">What experienced moms wish they knew</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="bcg-card-body">
        <div class="bcg-tip"><div class="bcg-tip-num green">1</div><p class="bcg-tip-text"><strong>Over-washing.</strong> 2–3 baths a week is enough for newborns. Too many strips natural oils.</p></div>
        <div class="bcg-tip"><div class="bcg-tip-num green">2</div><p class="bcg-tip-text"><strong>Using too much product.</strong> A pea-sized amount of lotion covers the entire body.</p></div>
        <div class="bcg-tip"><div class="bcg-tip-num green">3</div><p class="bcg-tip-text"><strong>Ignoring expiry dates.</strong> Baby wipes, creams, and formulas expire — check dates every time.</p></div>
        <div class="bcg-tip"><div class="bcg-tip-num green">4</div><p class="bcg-tip-text"><strong>Using powders near the face.</strong> Talc powder can be inhaled and cause lung issues. Avoid for under-2s.</p></div>
        <div class="bcg-tip"><div class="bcg-tip-num green">5</div><p class="bcg-tip-text"><strong>Not patch testing.</strong> Test new products on a small wrist area for 24 hours before full use.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>

  <a href="/collections/baby-care" class="bcg-back-btn">🛒 Shop Baby Care Products</a>

</section>

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Baby Care Guide",
  "settings": []
}
{% endschema %}
